The Model Context Protocol (MCP) allows AI assistants like Claude and ChatGPT to interact with Pipedrive CRM data [1]. Pipedrive has released a native MCP server [1], and several community-developed open-source servers are also available [2][3][4][5][6][7][8].

These servers enable natural language interactions for CRUD operations, CRM record management, and pipeline analysis [1][5][6]. Most implementations require a Pipedrive API token and support both v1 and v2 API endpoints to ensure compatibility with different Pipedrive entities [3][4][5][6]. Setup typically involves adding a configuration block to your MCP client settings:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "pipedrive": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "pipedrive-mcp-package-name"],
      "env": {
        "PIPEDRIVE_API_TOKEN": "your-api-token"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Consult the documentation for the specific repository you choose, as tool counts, architectural features, and configuration parameters vary significantly between implementations [3][5][6][8].
